<h1 title = "In HTML" > Inline CSS </h1> 
<p> <em> <mark> Inline CSS </mark> </em> is used to apply a unique style to a single  <abbr title="Hyper Text Markup Language"> HTML</abbr> element </p>
<h2 title = "In HTML"> Internal CSS </h2>
<p> An <strong> <mark> internal css </mark> </strong> is used to define the style for <del>many</del> single   <abbr title="Hyper Text Markup Language"> HTML</abbr> page. <br> It is defined in the <b><q> HEAD</q> </b> section of <abbr title="Hyper Text Markup Language"> HTML</abbr> page </p>
<h3 title = "In HTML"> External CSS </h3>
<p>  An external <ins> style sheet </ins> is used to define the style for many <abbr title="Hyper Text Markup Language"> HTML</abbr> pages.</p>
<h4 style="font-size:150%;"> Other elements <small> Subscript, Superscript</small> in<abbr title="Hyper Text Markup Language"> HTML</abbr>  </h4>
<ol>
<li> Subscript </li>
<hr>
<p> It defines the subscripted value.<br> Example = H <sub> 2 </sub> O </p>
<li> Superscript</li>
<hr>
<p> It defines the superscript value.<br> Example =  x<sup> 2 </sup>  </p>  
</ol>
